DialogueNode.dialogue: Hi, Janet. How're you doing today?
I'm pretty busy today. Is there anything you need?
Oh... no. Just saying hi. Good luck with your work!
Yes, actually. I overheard you talking to Dave...
Yes. I was wondering. How long have you been with Big Byte?
Pretty much since the beginning. Why do you ask?
Have there ever been any... issues between any of the current employees?
Well, since I'm pretty new around here, and don't have much context, I just wanted to know some more about your history with Big Byte.
I'd be happy to talk to you more about that later, but right now I'm slammed with work.
Of course, no worries! Good luck with your work.
I don't think so. I try not to get too invested in other people's personal business though.
That is an admirable quality. Just know that I'm here to help and that my door is always open.
Thank you. I'll be sure to pass the message along if anything comes up.
Ah, of course. It's just that I overheard you talking to Dave earlier and...
What? You know it's kinda rude to eavesdrop...
I just wanted to let you know that I'm here to deal with issues like this. If you wanted to talk with me about it, I'd be more than happy to do so.
Yes, of course. But it is my job to resolve issues between employees. I just want to make sure everything is ok.
Thanks, but I try not to get involved in my coworkers's personal business.
Try not to worry so much. Everything's fine.
Ok. Just remember, my door is always open. Good luck with your work.
